Because

 - `int` data type stores number from `-2^31` to `2^31 - 1`
 - `Integer` data type stores number from `-2^63` to `2^63 - 1`

Try with [BigInteger][1] 

    public static BigInteger fibonacci(int n) {
    	BigInteger[] f = new BigInteger[n + 1];
    	f[0] = BigInteger.ZERO;
    	if (n &gt; 0) {
    		f[1] = BigInteger.ONE;
    	}
    	for (int i = 2; i &lt; f.length; i++) {
    		f[i] = f[i - 1].add(f[i - 2]);
    	}
    	return f[n];
    }
But the 4 million Fibonacci value very long. See more [300th][2], [500th][3]


